  "text": "This necessity to introduce a specific notion of cut for each theory of interest has been an obstacle to the development of a general theory of cut elimination. Deduction modulo [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] has been an attempt to partially solve this problem. In deduction modulo, the axioms of the form ∀x 1 ... ∀x n (t = u) or ∀x 1 ... ∀x n (P ⇔ A) where P is an atomic proposition are replaced by rewrite rules t −→ u or P −→ A. For instance, the axiom P ⇔ (Q ⇒ R) is replaced by the rewrite rule P −→ (Q ⇒ R). Then, deduction is performed modulo the congruence generated by these rules. For instance, with the rewrite rule P −→ (Q ⇒ R), an instance of the elimination rule of the implication is",
